chester: Manchester University Press (2006).\n*Perez Zagorin, ''Rebels and Rulers, 1500\u20131660. Volume II: Provincial rebellion: Revolutionary civil wars, 1560\u20131660''. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press (1992).\n{{refend}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|20em}}\n{{EB1911|wstitle = Philip IV., king of Spain|volume=21}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.hispavox.com/FelipeIV/ La Pol\u00edtica Internacional de Felipe IV]\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-hou|[[Habsburg Spain|House of Habsburg]]|8 April|1605|17 September|1665}}\n{{s-reg}}\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before=[[Philip III of Spain]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Portuguese monarchs|King of Portugal]]|years=31 March 1621 \u2013 1 December 1640}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[John IV of Portugal|John IV]]}}\n|-\n{{s-ttl|title=[[King of Spain]] |years=31 March 1621 \u2013 17 September 1665}}\n{{s-aft|rows=2|after=[[Charles II of Spain]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before=[[Albert VII, Archduke of Austria|Albert]] and<br>[[Infanta Isabella Clara Eugenia of Spain|Isabella Clara Eugenia]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=|title=[[Duke of Milan]], [[Dukes of Lothier|Lothier]],<br>[[Dukes of Brabant|Brabant]], [[Dukes of Limburg|Limburg]] and [[Counts, Dukes and Grand Dukes of Luxembourg|Luxemburg]];<br>[[Count Palatine of Burgundy]];<br>[[Counts of Flanders|Count of Flanders]], [[Counts of Hainaut|Hainaut]] and [[Marquis of Namur|Namur]]|years=13 July 1621 \u2013 17 September 1665}}\n|-\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Count of Artois]]|years=13 July 1621 \u2013 7 November 1659}}\n{{s-non|reason=Lost to France<br><small>[[Treaty of the Pyrenees]]</small>}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Isabella Appiani|Isabella]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Principality of Piombino|Prince of Piombino]]|years=1628\u20131634}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Niccol\u00f2 I Ludovisi|Nicholas I]]}}\n{{s-roy}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Philip III of Spain|Philip]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Prince of Asturias]]|years=1605\u20131621}}\n{{s-aft|rows=2|after=[[Balthasar Charles, Prince of Asturias and Portugal|Balthasar Charles]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Anne 